{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In addition to the loss defined in Eq. 3, to further improve the domain invariant properties of the features (and thus reduce the divergence between domains), we apply an adversarial domain alignment (Ganin & Lempitsky, 2015; Wang et al., 2019).",
    "We follow the recipe used in other recent UDA work (Chen et al., 2019; Munro & Damen, 2020; Wei et al., 2022; Jamal et al., 2018), and introduce a classifier that predicts whether features are from the source or the target.",
    "This classifier is directly connected to the feature extractors via a Gradient Reversal Layer (GRL) (Ganin & Lempitsky, 2015).",
    "The domain classification loss L d is then multiplied by a weight λ d and added to the total loss.",
    "The loss we have introduced so far (i.e., the combination of L RNA and L d) aims to improve the informative and domain invariant properties of the embeddings of the different modalities."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
